    <pre>Some last things you need to do:

0. Take a look at <a href="http://openhatch.org/wiki/How_we_handle_patches">http://openhatch.org/wiki/How_we_handle_patches</a>

1. Make a local commit, and use "git format-patch" to turn that patch into a file.

That way, we get a commit log message, and you're the "Author".

2. Email Devel saying that you're okay with us using your work under AGPLv3 (or
later, if you like)

e.g. <a href="http://lists.openhatch.org/pipermail/devel/2011-March/001802.html">http://lists.openhatch.org/pipermail/devel/2011-March/001802.html</a>

Take care of the above, and we'll deploy this. I just tested it, and indeed this
does fix the problem. Thanks for this great patch!</pre>
